âœ… Basic Definition

React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces (UI) in a declarative and component-based way.


âœ… Basic Definition of Props

Props (short for â€œpropertiesâ€) are inputs to a React component that allow data to be passed from a parent component to a child component.


ğŸ†š State vs Props

| Feature        | Props                                          | State                                                    |
| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Definition** | Inputs to a component, passed from parent      | Internal data of a component                             |
| **Ownership**  | Owned by parent component                      | Owned by the component itself                            |
| **Mutability** | **Read-only** inside child                     | **Mutable**, can be updated with `setState` / `useState` |
| **Purpose**    | Customize or configure child component         | Store componentâ€™s dynamic data                           |
| **Updates**    | Changes when parent re-renders with new values | Changes with `setState` / `useState`, triggers re-render |
| **Usage**      | `<Child name="Shubham" />`                     | `const [count, setCount] = useState(0)`                  |
| **Example**    | Parent â†’ Child communication                   | Componentâ€™s own interactive behavior                     |
